  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        patients with a sleepiness evoking a primary hypersomnia
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Men or women aged &gt; 18 years

          -  Patient with a sleepiness evoking a primary hypersomnia

          -  Epworth sleepiness scale &gt; 10

          -  Information note signed

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Patient with type 1 or 2 narcolepsy and/or known hypersomnia

          -  Frank cataplexy

          -  Not stable metabolic, neurological or psychiatric disease

          -  Patient treated by a medicine acting on the central nervous system

          -  Patient having a shift work or having made a transmeridian flight of more than 3 hours
             lag in the previous month the research

          -  Non affiliation to social security

          -  Pregnancy

          -  Patient under guardianship or curatorship
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
